records.addlTxt: INELIGIBLE VOTING NOTICE AND ACKNOWLEDGEMENT. kl
NOTICE OF RIGHT TO SEEK POSTCOVICTION RELIEF. kl

Sentencing Proceeded. Statements by parties and defendant.

AS TO COUNT 1 AMENDED 
The court sentenced the defendant to 10 MONTHS in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence.

AS TO COUNT 2 AMENDED
Court withheld sentence. Court placed defendant on probation for 2 YEARS
with the following conditions:

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION
-Batterers Intervention program.
-Absolute sobriety.
-No contact with victim Veronica N. unless approved by court or agent.
-Obtain/maintain employment.
-No contact with firearms.
-Pay all MANDATORY court costs, fees, and surcharges including: DNA & DV surcharges during period of probation, failure to pay will result in a civil judgment. 
-Provide DNA Sample.

-Restitution in the amount of $4,608.84 to be paid to Veronica N during the period of probation. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment. 

*Court advised defendant of right to seek post conviction relief.
*Court advised defendant of penalties for violation of NO CONTACT ORDER.
*Court advised that under 48 USC Section 922(g)(9) the defendant is prohibited from possession of a firearm and/or ammunition after conviction of a crime of domestic violence.

 Court ordered defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.

AS TO COUNTS 1 AND 2
Defendant changes plea(s) to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to plea, advised of Constitutional Rights and the maximum penalties. Court found that the defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived rights.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights form, Addendum, and Jury Instructions, received and filed. Parties stipulate to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea(s).  Court found defendant GUILTY and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.
Received and Filed, Restitution paperwork.

Defendant Martin Ordoncz Castillo in court with attorney Awni M Yasin.  Defendant Martin Ordoncz Castillo in custody.  Nicolas J Heitman appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Sworn as interpreter: Ruth Garcia. Parties have reached a resolution. 

AS TO COUNTS 1 AND 2
Purusant to plea negotiations, on motion of the State, Court ordered charge amended to Battery, Repeater, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 940.19(1) and 939.62(1)(b), a Class A Misdemeanor.
